Some Cocoa Traders May Pay Export Taxes to Gbagbo, Financial Times Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-22T02:52:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/some-cocoa-traders-may-pay-export-taxes-to-gbagbo-financial-times-reports.html
Some cocoa traders are planning to
pay export taxes to Ivory Coast President  Laurent Gbagbo ’s
regime amid concern Gbagbo may expropriate $1.3 billion worth of
cocoa stocks if they don’t submit payments by the end of March,
the Financial Times said.  Noble Group Ltd. (NOBL)  plans to pay the taxes, the FT also
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer, Ricardo Leiman. Noble
later clarified that the company’s actions would be guided by
its legal advice, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 